{\*\bkmkstart Eloise}Eloise{\*\bkmkend Eloise} Sullivan missed having a man in her life. \
\
It\'92s been ten years since her husband, Roger, died. She could count her number of dates on one hand, with fingers to spare.\
\
At first, it was all she could do to look after their daughter, Billie. At least, the generous ICE pension paid the bills. Now, with working as a monitor part-time, she\'92s starting to get ahead.\
\
As Billie grew older, she began to wonder: \'93
\f1\i Where does a single mom meet an unattached man?
\f0\i0 \'94\
\
Coming in through the kitchen door, her daughter asked, \'93Hi, mom, what\'92s for dinner?\'94\
\
\'93The store had Wyoming Beef today, so I made meatloaf.\'94\
\
\'93Yum, are there any green beans?\'94\
\
\'93Not today, but we can have Idaho Freedom Fries. \'97 How was school?\'94\
\
\'93About that \'85 There was an incident.\'94\
\
\'93You mean a shooting? I didn\'92t hear anything.\'94\
\
\'93Not a shooting. But there was an altercation between two students.\'94\
\
\'93Was anyone hurt?\'94\
\
\'93No, a drone broke it up, and security grabbed the kids.\'94\
\
\'93Was it anyone you know?\'94\
\
\'93Kinda. It was two girls.\'94\
\
Eloise made a tsk-tsk sound with her tongue.\
\
\'93The first girl posted something about the second girl\'92s mom online. Second girl asked first girl to take it down. First girl refused. Second girl pushed her. Drone broke it up.\'94\
\
\'93Did anyone get tased?\'94\
\
\'93No. Security brought them to the principal.\'94\
\
\'93I feel bad for the parents.\'94\
\
\'93Me too,\'94 says Billie, handing her mom a tablet.\
\
\'93What\'92s this?\'94\
\
\'93I was the second girl. Maddie Fox posted a meme of you online and wouldn\'92t take it down. It\'92s in an attachment.\'94\
\
Eloise opens the attachment. It\'92s a character from an old cartoon. A rat is standing like a person with pointed ears, wearing a red robe with a black belt. The hands and feet are furry paws. In one paw-hand, there is a wooden cane. A pointed, ribbed tail snakes out from the back of the robe. Over what would be the rat\'92s snout, Eloise\'92s face is crudely pasted.\
\
\'93Maddie said her mom didn\'92t cut the grass enough, and you reduced her benefits.\'94\
\
\'93Monitors don\'92t control  benefits, but if she was already low on points, I guess it could happen.\'94\
\
\'93Can you make the meeting with the principal tomorrow? It\'92s mandatory when a drone is involved.\'94\
\
\'93I guess I\'92ll have to,\'94 Eloise replies, wondering how Billie got the upper hand.\
